Implement the public `merge/2` function for the `BloomFilter` module.

`merge/2` takes two `BloomFilter` structs and returns a new filter whose bit
array is the bitwise-OR of the two inputs' bit arrays, representing the union of
both filters' item sets. Both filters must have been created with identical
parameters: use a head that pattern-matches the same `m` and `k` on both structs
to combine them, and OR their `bits` word-by-word. Because `bits` is stored as a
tuple of 64-bit integer words, convert both tuples to lists, zip them together,
`Bitwise.bor/2` each corresponding pair of words, and turn the result back into a
tuple. Return the first filter with its `:bits` field replaced by the merged
tuple.

Provide a second clause that matches any two `BloomFilter` structs whose
parameters do not line up (i.e. differing `m` or `k`) and raises an
`ArgumentError` whose message reports the `m` and `k` of each filter, so callers
